@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Proclamation of Privacy";
}

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h1 class="card-title">Royal Proclamation of Privacy</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-10">
                <div class="alert alert-primary">
                    <div class="d-flex">
                        <div class="me-3">
                            <i class="fas fa-shield-alt fa-2x text-primary"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="alert-heading">Thy Privacy During the Someren Pilgrimage</h4>
                            <p class="mb-0">Hark! The Someren scrolls doth process personal particulars of scholars and masters participating in the annual Computer Sciences guild pilgrimage. This decree outlineth how we handle such sacred information.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3">Gathering of Information</h3>
                <p>The Someren parchments doth collect and process these manner of records:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Scholar information (apprentice number, Christian name and family name, messenger pigeon contact, apprentice guild)</li>
                    <li>Master information (Christian name and family name, messenger pigeon contact, years since birth)</li>
                    <li>Chamber assignments in the East and West keeps</li>
                    <li>Tournament participation and oversight ledgers</li>
                    <li>Tavern transactions (drink tokens and mead consumption)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3">How We Employ Thy Records</h3>
                <p>Thy records are used exclusively for:</p>
                <div class="row mt-3 mb-4">
                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                        <div class="p-3 border rounded bg-light text-center">
                            <i class="fas fa-users text-primary mb-3" style="font-size: 2rem;"></i>
                            <h5>Pilgrimage Governance</h5>
                            <p class="small mb-0">Arranging lodgings and tournaments</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                        <div class="p-3 border rounded bg-light text-center">
                            <i class="fas fa-bed text-primary mb-3" style="font-size: 2rem;"></i>
                            <h5>Chamber Bestowment</h5>
                            <p class="small mb-0">Administering quarters and sleeping chambers</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                        <div class="p-3 border rounded bg-light text-center">
                            <i class="fas fa-cash-register text-primary mb-3" style="font-size: 2rem;"></i>
                            <h5>Tavern Operations</h5>
                            <p class="small mb-0">Tracking mead tokens and provisions</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3">Token and Tavern Records</h3>
                <p>By decree of the Crown and tax collectors, we track libation consumption at the Monday eve revelry. This includeth:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Manner of drinks procured (spirits and non-spirits)</li>
                    <li>Royal tax calculations (9% for water and juices, 21% for spirits and mead)</li>
                    <li>Token redemption chronicles</li>
                    <li>Tavern duty assignments for masters</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3">Record Preservation</h3>
                <p>Personal scrolls are retained only for the duration necessary to orchestrate and oversee the Someren pilgrimage. Tournament and tavern records may be kept longer for the royal accountants and tax collectors as required by the King's law.</p>

                <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3">Protection of Records</h3>
                <p>We implementeth appropriate safeguards to protect all personal chronicles regarding scholars, masters, lodgings, tournaments, and tavern operations.</p>

                <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3">Guild Access</h3>
                <p>These scrolls are accessible only to authorized Computer Sciences guild masters responsible for orchestrating and governing the Someren pilgrimage.</p>

                <div class="alert alert-light border mt-5">
                    <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Last updated: In the year of our Lord two thousand five and twenty, during the third moon. This privacy decree applieth specifically to the Someren parchments and related activities.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>